{
  "stem": "21786.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were watched and guarded from above, and we had special kinds of passes to pass outside of Theresien.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I became a foreman, and I had a pass with-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think at that point it was still my name-- plus 14 other Jews.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I moved at that point.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We found a space.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We have-- were four young guys, and we found a space directly in the walls of this big fortress.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It's a horse stables, and the horse hands were living there in rooms which would be, I mean, about three by four square-- three-- three by four meters, with one huge window leading into a hall that all was-- was in the walls of-- of the fortress.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But it was outside of the ghetto itself, but not-- still inside of the guarded circle [INAUDIBLE] by the gendarmes, so we didn't need any special passes.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We had to chisel a window so that it would-- all the conditions of the department of health, which was there in the ghetto, would-- we would comply with it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we were four young men.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Two of them went with me all through, through Auschwitz and through Schwarzheide and the death march.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the fourth one went through a different routing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The tragedy of this, which I want to mention, is that they all survived.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And all three of my friends, one of them here in Montreal, committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They all died by hanging them-- them-- themselves.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Egon, E-G-O-N, did it in Prague about six years after the war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "My friend [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] George [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] hanged himself in the year 1982.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
